            "title": "Games and Bereavement : How Video Games Represent Attachment, Loss and Grief",
            "abstract": "How can videogames portray love and loss? \u00bbGames and Bereavement\u00ab answers this question by analysing five videogames and conducting a participatory design study with grievers. Sabine Harrer offers both theoretical and practical perspectives on videogames and grief and suggests a design model for videogames to include grievers into game development. Overall, she explores how videogames can be used as contemporary medium for personal storytelling",
